## BACKLOG-021 - Show git and PR links on tickets
- Status: Grooming
- Owner: Paula Product
- Requester: current session
- Date added: 2026-04-13
- Updated: 2026-04-14T08:50:44.305Z
- Due Date: 
- Priority: P1
- Effort: 2
- Sprint Assigned: Sprint 7
- Ready for Implementation?: No
- Tech handoff owner: Ben
- Summary: Show each ticket's git link and PR link in the ticket UI when traceability metadata exists.
- Outcome / user value: Users can jump from a backlog ticket to active implementation work without searching across tools or guessing which branch or PR matches the story.
- Scope notes: In scope, resolving the git URL and PR URL from integration-derived traceability metadata keyed by `BACKLOG-XXX`, with the git destination taken from the linked branch or commit URL in that metadata and the PR destination taken from the linked pull-request URL in that metadata. In scope, showing the available link when only one exists, showing a calm no-link helper when neither exists, and keeping any existing editor preview as a separate helper rather than replacing it with traceability links. Open question, the ticket-editor helper contract decision still needs to define how the existing helper and the traceability links coexist. Out of scope, editing the markdown schema, requiring manual URL entry on stories, inventing a second source of truth for traceability URLs, or removing the editor preview as part of this ticket.
- Acceptance criteria:
  - [ ] A ticket resolves its git URL from the integration-derived branch or commit destination associated with that `BACKLOG-XXX` item.
  - [ ] A ticket resolves its PR URL from the integration-derived pull-request destination associated with that `BACKLOG-XXX` item.
  - [ ] If only the git URL exists, the ticket shows the git link and a calm missing-PR helper state.
  - [ ] If only the PR URL exists, the ticket shows the PR link and a calm missing-git helper state.
  - [ ] If neither URL exists yet, the ticket presents a clear no-link state instead of empty or confusing UI.
  - [ ] The links are visibly associated with the ticket they belong to and can be opened directly from the ticket UI.
  - [ ] Any existing editor preview remains available as a separate helper and is not replaced by the traceability links.
  - [ ] The ticket remains readable and compact, with traceability links presented as supporting actions rather than replacing core story content.
- Dependencies: BACKLOG-020, BACKLOG-023, traceability metadata availability, traceability metadata lookup contract, ticket-editor helper contract decision.
- Links: current session request
- Implementation notes: Blocked with no implementation work started and no repo changes yet. Waiting on the traceability metadata needed to resolve ticket-linked destinations and on the ticket-editor helper contract decision before this can return to `Ready`.

