## BACKLOG-039 - Warn before switching projects during active Paula work
- Status: Ready
- Owner: Paula Product
- Requester: current session
- Date added: 2026-04-14
- Updated: 2026-04-14T08:49:44.245Z
- Due Date: 
- Priority: P1
- Effort: 1
- Sprint Assigned: Sprint 7
- Ready for Implementation?: Yes
- Tech handoff owner: Ben
- Summary: Show a clear warning before users switch projects while Paula is actively working on the current board.
- Outcome / user value: Users can avoid interrupting or abandoning active grooming work by mistake when they switch to another project.
- Scope notes: In scope, detecting an active Paula session at project-switch time, presenting a confirmation warning before the switch completes, and making the consequence legible in plain language. In scope, allowing the user to either stay on the current project or continue with the switch after confirmation. Out of scope, redesigning Paula session management, preserving one Paula run across projects, or introducing a hard block that prevents all switching.
- Acceptance criteria:
  - [ ] If Paula is actively working on the current board, initiating a project switch shows a warning before the switch completes.
  - [ ] The warning states that Paula is still working on the current project and that switching projects may interrupt that backlog session.
  - [ ] The warning offers a clear stay action and a clear continue-switch action.
  - [ ] Choosing the stay action leaves the user on the current project with the active Paula session unchanged.
  - [ ] Choosing the continue-switch action completes the project switch without showing the warning again during the same user action.
  - [ ] If Paula is not actively working, the project switch continues without showing the warning.
- Dependencies: BACKLOG-002, project switch flow, Paula active-session state.
- Links: current session request
- Implementation notes: Leave blank until the item is `Ready` or in execution

## BACKLOG-041 - Sort epic and sprint selectors by numeric value
- Status: Ready
- Owner: Paula Product
- Requester: current session
- Date added: 2026-04-14
- Updated: 2026-04-14T08:49:39.985Z
- Due Date: 
- Priority: P1
- Effort: 1
- Sprint Assigned: Sprint 7
- Ready for Implementation?: Yes
- Tech handoff owner: Ben
- Summary: Sort epic and sprint options by their numeric value instead of relying on lexical ordering or mixed label text.
- Outcome / user value: Users can trust selector ordering when epics and sprints reach double digits or include labels that otherwise sort incorrectly as plain text.
- Scope notes: In scope, sorting epic selector options by increasing numeric value and sorting sprint selector options by decreasing numeric value so newer sprints remain first. In scope, extracting the numeric portion from labels that follow the established `Epic N` and `Sprint N` pattern. Out of scope, renaming labels, changing assignment semantics, or redefining which sprint counts as current.
- Acceptance criteria:
  - [ ] Epic selector options sort by the numeric value in the epic label rather than plain-text order.
  - [ ] Sprint selector options sort by the numeric value in the sprint label rather than plain-text order.
  - [ ] Epic options with labels `Epic 2`, `Epic 10`, and `Epic 11` appear in numeric order rather than `Epic 10` before `Epic 2`.
  - [ ] Sprint options with labels `Sprint 2`, `Sprint 10`, and `Sprint 11` appear newest first by numeric value.
  - [ ] Labels that do not expose a usable numeric value fall back to stable plain-text ordering after numeric labels.
- Dependencies: BACKLOG-025, epic selector ordering, sprint selector ordering, numeric label parsing rule, BACKLOG-040.
- Links: current session request
- Implementation notes: Leave blank until the item is `Ready` or in execution

## BACKLOG-042 - Reset invalid Current Sprint after board changes
- Status: Ready
- Owner: Paula Product
- Requester: current session
- Date added: 2026-04-14
- Updated: 2026-04-14T08:40:44.000Z
- Due Date: 
- Priority: P0
- Effort: 2
- Sprint Assigned: 
- Ready for Implementation?: Yes
- Tech handoff owner: Ben
- Summary: Recover the Current Sprint selector when a board change leaves it pointing at a sprint value that the new board cannot represent.
- Outcome / user value: Users can switch to a board with fewer sprints without getting stuck on an empty Current Sprint value that cannot be changed.
- Scope notes: In scope, detecting when a carried-over Current Sprint value is invalid for the newly opened board, resetting the selector to a valid option, and keeping the selector interactive after the board switch. In scope, preserving the previous selection only when that sprint still exists on the new board. Out of scope, changing valid sprint selections that still exist on the new board or redesigning the entire Current Sprint panel.
- Acceptance criteria:
  - [ ] If a board switch leaves Current Sprint set to a value that does not exist on the new board, the selector recovers to a valid state automatically.
  - [ ] After recovery, users can still open the selector and choose any valid sprint on the new board.
  - [ ] If the previously selected sprint is still valid on the new board, the board preserves that selection.
  - [ ] If the previous Current Sprint is invalid and the new board has selectable sprints, the selector resets to the highest available sprint on that board.
  - [ ] If the new board has no selectable sprints, the selector shows a clear empty state and remains usable when sprint options appear later.
- Dependencies: BACKLOG-018, board switch flow, current sprint selector state, sprint option hydration.
- Links: current session request
- Implementation notes: Leave blank until the item is `Ready` or in execution

