## BACKLOG-002 - Show Paula session launch and run state
- Status: Done
- Owner: Paula Product
- Requester: repo-local backlog seed
- Date added: 2026-04-13
- Updated: 2026-04-13T23:45:13.451Z
- Due Date: 
- Priority: P1
- Effort: 2
- Sprint Assigned: Sprint 5
- Ready for Implementation?: Yes
- Tech handoff owner: Ben
- Summary: Expose whether the latest Paula launch succeeded, is still running, or has already ended.
- Outcome / user value: Users can trust the backlog grooming flow because the UI makes it clear whether Paula is actively working or the launch failed.
- Scope notes: In scope, a minimal visible status for the latest Paula session covering launch attempt, active run state, and terminal failure or completion. Out of scope, a full chat redesign, multi-session history, or detailed process logs.
- Acceptance criteria:
  - [ ] After a user launches Paula, the UI shows a visible status for the latest session instead of leaving the launch outcome implicit.
  - [ ] A successful launch is distinguishable from a failed launch, so users can tell whether Paula actually started.
  - [ ] While the latest Paula session is still active, the UI shows that it is running and does not imply the work is already finished.
  - [ ] If `codex` is unavailable or the launched process exits before a usable Paula response is produced, the UI shows a clear failed state for that latest session.
  - [ ] When the latest Paula session ends after running, the UI no longer presents it as active.
- Dependencies: Paula agent launch endpoint, latest-session process tracking.
- Links: server/index.ts, docs/UX_PRODUCT_OWNER_PROMPT.md
